<dl id="sa0512m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="sa" href="#sa0512m">SA (VI.A) </a>: <a href="../../ff/fnbs/ssaall.htm#sa0512m"> 512(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> give that to me &amp; be a fool yrself:</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;<mark>Give that to me and be a fool yourself</mark>.&rsquo; Said of a request which is thought unreasonable. <small> Thomas F. O'Rahilly, <a name="TFOR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TFOR"><cite title="source">A Miscellany of Irish Proverbs</cite></a> (Dublin: Talbot Press, 1922) 35, &para;125</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
